ABOUT US

Glenunga Uniting Church is a diverse congregation from a wide variety of cultures and backgrounds, and ages from naught to ninty. We love to see new people, and all are welcome to join in. No matter who you are, you will find friends, groups and ministries to welcome you and help you grow in life and faith. We have programs for children, youth, families, adults, people just arrived from other countries and more.

At Glenunga we often talk about being "Your Wider Family", and we hope that will be your experience with us - being part of a wider family that cares for and supports each other as we worship Jesus together.

OUR CONGREGATION

Glenunga is a reletively small congregation of around fifty - adding to the family feel. Our congregation includes toddlers, pensioners, and everything in between. We have members and families from a wide variety of cultures and backgrounds, and consider our multicultural make-up one of our strengths.

OUR CORE VALUES

Our community is united around our core values - four principals that define who we are as a church, and what we value as a community.
